g.text: 6.1 Segemntation model generates boxes and masks
6.2 Find the dominant color in the image (returns dominant color + image where dominant color is (255, 255, 255)
6.3a Measure fixed scale images via colorboard (returns pixels per cm for that image)
6.3b Measure random scale images via largest square contour algorithm (returns pixels per cm for that image)
6.4 Loop over the masks (if there is more than 1) (returns list with tupels of mask, cm² of that mask)
6.5 Loop over the boxes and get the height and width in cm (returns list with tupel of box, and a dict of width_cm and height_cm)
6.6 Crop and mask out the images (returns list with tupel of masked out image and cropped out image)
6.7 Images are saved in RGBA format, where every pixel that is >= 250 is being turned into a transparant pixel
6.8 Cm² is calculated again for the RGBA image so it doesn't take into account the white pixels (which it did before)
7. Improve cm² calculation by filling in tapes on plants
8. Start with more precise segmentation (leafes, stems, roots, etc...
not all boards are always detected
